<h2 id="category">Category</h2>

<p>A Category is a node in a Classification Tree that represents a logical grouping of related Classifications.
For example, &lsquo;iPhone&rsquo; and &#39;Tablet&rsquo; Classifications might both be children of a &#39;Device&rsquo; Category.
There is a limit to 20 levels of depth for Categories.</p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th style="text-align: left">Name</th>
<th style="text-align: left">Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left">Id (<code class="prettyprint">Integer</code>)</td>
<td style="text-align: left">Identifier</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left">Name (<code class="prettyprint">String</code>)</td>
<td style="text-align: left">Name</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left">Categories (<code class="prettyprint">Array[object]</code>)</td>
<td style="text-align: left">Child Categories</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left">Classifications (<code class="prettyprint">Array[object]</code>)</td>
<td style="text-align: left">Child Classifications</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: left">Order (<code class="prettyprint">Integer</code>)</td>
<td style="text-align: left">Sorting order</td>
</tr>
